    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"subheading1\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>Scalability Targets",
      "pos": [
        8052,
        8097
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Each of the Azure Storage services has scalability targets for capacity (GB), transaction rate, and bandwidth.",
      "pos": [
        8098,
        8208
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If your application approaches or exceeds any of the scalability targets, it may encounter increased transaction latencies or throttling.",
      "pos": [
        8209,
        8346
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When a Storage service throttles your application, the service begins to return “503 Server busy” or “500 Operation timeout” error codes for some storage transactions.",
      "pos": [
        8347,
        8514
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This section discusses both the general approach to dealing with scalability targets and bandwidth scalability targets in particular.",
      "pos": [
        8515,
        8648
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Later sections that deal with individual storage services discuss scalability targets in the context of that specific service:",
