      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "At the time of writing, the bandwidth targets in the US for a geo-redundant storage (GRS) account are 10 gigabits per second (Gbps) for ingress (data sent to the storage account) and 20 Gbps for egress (data sent from the storage account).",
      "pos": [
        9014,
        9253
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For a locally redundant storage (LRS) account, the limits are higher – 20 Gbps for ingress and 30 Gbps for egress.",
      "pos": [
        9254,
        9368
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "International bandwidth limits may be lower and can be found on our <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>scalability targets page<ept id=\"p1\">](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/azure/dn249410.aspx)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
